## Fix Report: security-analyst

**Root Cause**: API usage quota exhaustion — not a code bug.

The security-analyst ran **successfully** in the first swarm run (`21-16-13`), producing a comprehensive report (93/100 security score, all scans passing, compliance mapped). The second swarm run (`21-24-11`) failed because the Claude API returned "You're out of extra usage" — the platform-level usage quota was exhausted before the agent could even start.

**Resolution**: No code fix is possible or needed. The agent is healthy. Options:
1. Wait for the quota to reset (midnight AEST)
2. Upgrade the API usage tier
3. Space out swarm runs to avoid hitting limits with back-to-back runs (the two runs were only ~8 minutes apart: 21:16 and 21:24)

Fix report written to `.claude/team-state/fix-security-analyst-status.md`.
